// Phone-and-person search cluster — CPC (Act 593) + Police Act 1967 (PA1967).
// Flagship: "can a police officer go through my phone?" The honest core:
// CPC s116B is an EXPRESS computerized-data access power (incl. passwords) —
// but only for Inspector+ AND only riding on a lawful search under the Code
// (s20 arrest search, s116/s116A, warrant). The roadblock itself (PA s24/s26)
// grounds licence production + vehicle search, not phone contents.
// cpc-03 is an arrest-quadruple tripwire: the CPC general power must not be
// crowded out by the DDA/MOA arrest lookalikes.
